snippet.textDisplay:
In the hidden alcoves of my heart’s embrace,  
I’ve sheltered your memories with tender grace,  
Nestled deep where they shimmer and glow,  
Unforgotten, a sacred space where they flow.  

Our whispered conversations, gently preserved,  
In the sanctum of my soul, lovingly curved,  
I’ve enshrined your name in a breath’s soft sigh,  
With a reverent hush and a tearful eye.  

This solitude, a silent penance I bear,  
A testament of pain, a lament so rare,  
You are the balm to my sorrowful plight,  
Feel my love’s warmth in the day’s golden light.  

As seasons shift and faces change their hue,  
Witness the world’s transformations anew,  
So does my love for you remain unfeigned,  
In the quiet corners of my heart, ever sustained.
